# WordPress Sites Configuration for check_wordpress
# Format: name;path;webuser;php-binary
#
# name        - Short identifier for the site (used as argument to check_wordpress_site.sh)
# path        - Absolute path to the WordPress installation (where wp-config.php lives)
# webuser     - System user that owns the WordPress files (WP-CLI runs as this user)
# php-binary  - PHP binary to use (e.g., php, php8.2, php8.3)
#
# Lines starting with # are ignored.

# mysite;/var/www/mysite.example.com/web;www-data;php8.3
# blog;/var/www/blog.example.com/htdocs;web101;php8.2
